Task:
Extract and list ONLY the Requirement components (R) contained in this rule.
Definitions (RASE):

Requirement (R): a mandatory condition the design must meet.
Exception (E): a clause that modifies/replaces a requirement for a specific case.
Output format:
Provide only a numbered list.
Each line must be one requirement in one of these two forms:

Requirement: <text>
Requirement (within Exception): <text> (only if the requirement is stated inside an exception clause)
Do NOT include Applicability, Selection, or Exception statements as standalone items.
