34;2_3;rules_understanding;ambiguity;multichoice;{correct_option_index};"This regulation is ambiguous. Which main category of ambiguity does it belong to?

Categories:
1 ""Unintentional ambiguity � Use of language"" appears because natural language is inherently imprecise.
2 ""Unintentional ambiguity � Tacit knowledge"" refers to the implicit, experience-based knowledge that is embedded in building requirements but is not fully written down, formalized, or explicitly stated. 
3 ""Unintentional ambiguity � ACC-specific"" Requirements in
this category, if taken out of the ACC context, are unambiguous
and can be easily understood by humans without the possibility of
other interpretations. They only become ambiguous because there
is ambiguity in mapping objects/relationships in requirements to
objects/relationships in the design model.

Rule:
{rule_text_atomic}

Choose one: 1- ""Use of language"", 2 -""Tacit knowledge"",  3 -""ACC-specific"", or ""4"" for None of them

